column2: All participants must be 18 years or older to participate.
column4:
I consent to my answers being recorded and used for data analysis and research purposes. 

Note: All information is anonymous
column5:
Are you currently enrolled or have taken a psychology course in community college? (Campus does not matter.)

Note: If you are enrolled in multiple courses, please choose one course to think about throughout the survey. 

If this does not apply, do not continue the survey, do not upload anything.
column6:
How many times do you typically verbally participate in your psychology course?

For example: Raising your hand, adding a comment to the material, asking a question, or offering an opinion.
column7: Do most students in the classroom participate more, the same, or less than you?
column8: Over the course of the semester, how often do you pay attention during your psychology lectures?
column9: How confident are you in your abilities to succeed in a psychology course?
column10:
If course has been completed: What grade did you receive?

If you are still enrolled in the course: What grade do you currently have?
